Kisii Senator Prof Sam Ongeri has asked the Judiciary to support the war on corruption. Speaking during a burial ceremony in Nyamira county where Chief Justice David Maraga was in attendance, he said the vice is hurting the economy and robbing the youth ofÂ  jobs and a future. He praised the move by President Uhuru Kenyatta and the National Super Alliance (Nasa) leader Raila Odinga for uniting to fight the vice saying majority of Kenyans are behind them.